description: Number of distinct products ijk with 0 <= i,j,k <= n.
links: T. D. Noe, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..200
prog: (Haskell)import Data.List (nub)a027426 n = length $ nub [i*j*k | i <- [0..n], j <- [0..n], k <- [0..n]]-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jan 01 2012(PARI) pr(n)=my(v=List());for(i=1,n, for(j=i,n, listput(v, i*j))); Set(v)a(n)=my(v=pr(n),u=v); for(i=2,n,u=Set(concat(u,v*i))); #u+1 \\ _Charles R Greathouse IV_, Mar 04 2014
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_.
